<TEXT>
<P>
 Anatoly Alexandrov, who led the Soviet effort to develop nuclear reactors such 
as the one that exploded at Chernobyl in 1986, died Thursday.He was 90. 
</P>
<P>
 Alexandrov was also instrumental in developing the Soviet nuclear-powered 
fleet. 
</P>
<P>
 He was head of the Kurchatov Institute, Russia's primary nuclear research 
center, and was president of the Soviet Academy of Sciences for 12 years. 
