<HEADLINE>
<P>
FREEWAY CHARGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 No added sales tax, please. The last temporary quarter-cent sales tax turned 
out to be a permanent tax. If we need to raise $700 million to get the 
earthquake grant, let us do it in a temporary and common sense way.Charge $1 
per vehicle on cars entering the freeways; that will cost $10 per week to 
drivers needing to use freeways. It will keep off ones that can use other means 
of travel. Do this until the needed $700 million is paid off, then remove the 
tax. What needs caution is to avoid the greedy officials wanting to continue 
the tax after the needed amount is paid off. 
</P>
<P>
 This will have several advantages; it will be a temporary tax, it will thin 
out traffic and it will allow quicker repair of broken freeways. 
</P>
<P>
 A. J. WHITE 
