<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANAHEIM ARENA GETS SOCCER TEAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A yet-to-be named indoor soccer team will play at Anaheim Arena beginning in 
June, it was announced Sunday.The team will play a 28-game schedule in the 
14-team Continental Indoor Soccer League. 
</P>
<P>
 The Ogden Corporation, which operates the arena, acquired the rights to the 
existing Los Angeles United franchise and is moving it to Anaheim. 
</P>
<P>
 The soccer team joins the Mighty Ducks and the Roller Hockey International 
Bullfrogs as the arena's tenants. 
</P>
</TEXT>
