<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROCKETS CALL OFF THREE-PLAYER TRADE AFTER THE PISTONS' ELLIOTT FAILS PHYSICAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Houston Rockets on Sunday called off their trade for Detroit Piston 
forward Sean Elliott after he failed to pass a physical. 
</P>
<P>
 Rocket Coach Rudy Tomjanovich would not say what part of the physical Elliott 
had failed. 
</P>
<P>
 The 6-foot-8 forward was traded Friday for forwards Robert Horry and Matt 
Bullard. He took a physical Saturday in Houston, then Rocket physician Bruce 
Moseley requested additional tests. 
</P>
<P>
 Elliott, who had knee surgery in high school, plays with braces on both knees. 
Last season, playing for the San Antonio Spurs, he sat out 12 games because of 
back problems. He sat out his last four games with the Pistons because of 
pneumonia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
