PACIFIC WATCH: TAIWAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Firm Joins Race for Asia's Cable TV Viewers: Po Hsin Entertainment Inc. 
announced it will launch Taiwan's first cable channel aimed at the growing 
television audience in the region. Po Hsin, 45% owned by Taiwan's ruling 
Nationalist Party, hopes to begin broadcasting Chinese-language news and 
entertainment throughout China, Taiwan and Southeast Asia in October on the 
Apstar-1 satellite, scheduled to be launched this summer. APT Satellite Co., a 
Beijing-controlled satellite concern based in Hong Kong, signed an agreement 
with Po Hsin to provide the satellite space, in a rare business pact between 
the Nationalist Party and a Mainland-controlled company. 
</P>
