<HEADLINE>
<P>
CORPORATE SNAPSHOT: ROCKWELL, SEAL BEACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nature of business: Multi-industry high technology company 
</P>
<P>
 Total employees: 77,000 
</P>
<P>
 In Orange County: 6,700 
</P>
<P>
 Stock listing in The Times: On NYSE "Rockwl" 
</P>
<P>
 Ticker symbol: "ROK" 
</P>
<P>
 Friday's stock close: $40.88 
</P>
<P>
 One-week change: Up $0.75 
</P>
<P>
 Analyst review: "Rockwell has proven to the world that whatever it does is 
well thought out, and usually very beneficial to the shareholder. It is run by 
some very smart people. The balance sheet is in good shape and it will be 
interesting to see what it does with its cash since its acquisition of 
Allen-Bradley in 1985 is paying off well for it now. The problem with investors 
is that when they hear about an acquisition, they expect to see immediate 
results. But sometimes it takes awhile. Rockwell has done an excellent job 
moving into non-defense industries. It is one of the few companies that has 
done a good job of diversifying. It hasn't gotten bogged down by not knowing 
how to sell to other markets." 
</P>
