<HEADLINE>
<P>
INSIDE JOB: OCCUPATION: CREATIVE DIRECTOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Name: Julie Ann Macias 
</P>
<P>
 Company: Creative Design Consultants 
</P>
<P>
 Job description: "I oversee the creative planning of model home interiors. I 
am responsible for keeping each project on track for the preliminary and final 
presentations. I interact with our clients and supervise a research staff." 
</P>
<P>
 Thumbs up: "I like the ever-changing nature of the design field. We have 
repeat customers, and that forces me to be even more creative when coming up 
with a design because we don't want to offer the same look twice. That means 
keeping up with what's new in color, texture and customer tastes." 
</P>
<P>
 Thumbs down: "It is very demanding to remain focused and bring all the details 
together for a presentation. Sometimes we present our ideas to as many as four 
clients in a week. You have to work well under pressure." 
</P>
<P>
 Next step: "I have spent a lot of time learning about design, and now I would 
like to learn more about marketing. That involves studying what appeals to 
customers and finding ways to create a memorable aspect for each model home." 
</P>
<P>
 Advice: "It helps to get a variety of experience early in your career. Every 
firm has its own approach, and it's important to know how to achieve a number 
of looks." 
</P>
<P>
 Salary range: Beginning designers start at slightly more than $20,000. Senior 
designers and project managers can earn nearly $40,000. 
</P>
<P>
 Hours: "When we have a presentation to give, we spend a lot of extra time 
perfecting it. At a busy firm, you are going to put in more than the standard 
workday now and then." 
</P>
<P>
 Educational and training requirements: Community colleges, including Orange 
Coast College in Costa Mesa, offer two-year programs in design. The Fashion 
Institute of Design and Merchandising and UCLA Extension in Los Angeles also 
offer two-year programs. 
</P>
<P>
 Major employing industries: Interior design firms. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information: Contact the American Society of Interior Designers at 
(714) 643-1549; the Fashion Institute of Design and Merchandising at (213) 
624-1200; Orange Coast College's Interior Design Program at (714) 432-5702; or 
UCLA Extension at (310) 825-8423. 
</P>
<P>
 Researched by JANICE L. JONES / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
