<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN SHOT DURING DISPUTE IN PACOIMA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man was shot and seriously wounded during an argument on a Pacoima street 
early Sunday morning, Los Angeles police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim, whose name was not released, was allegedly shot by Laborio 
Cassillas, 39, after he struck and injured Cassillas during an argument in 
front of 11803 Glenoaks Blvd. about 1 a.m. Sunday, said Officer Lorie Taylor, 
an LAPD spokeswoman. 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses chased down Cassillas and held him until authorities arrived. He was 
arrested at the scene, Taylor said. 
</P>
<P>
 "There were two victims down on the ground when officers arrived," Taylor 
said. "Ends up one was shot by the other." 
</P>
<P>
 Cassillas, who was being treated at County-USC Medical Center, has been 
charged with attempted murder, Taylor said. 
</P>
<P>
 The man who was shot was taken to Holy Cross Medical Center in Mission Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 Both men were in stable condition Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
