<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; PALMDALE MAN, 21, DIES OF GUNSHOT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 21-year-old Palmdale man died Sunday after being shot in a confrontation 
with another man, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Mickey Elliott died about 4 p.m. at Antelope Valley Hospital Medical Center in 
Lancaster from a gunshot wound to the head inflicted during a confrontation 
with another man Friday in the 38100 block of 11th Street East in Palmdale, 
said Deputy Donna Levi of the Los Angeles County Sheriff's Antelope Valley 
station. 
</P>
<P>
 Matthew Nall, 39, also of Palmdale, was booked on suspicion of attempted 
murder Friday at the Antelope Valley Sheriff's Station in connection with the 
shooting, Levi said. 
</P>
<P>
 In most cases, an attempted murder charge is changed to a murder charge when 
the victim dies. 
</P>
