<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: FULLERTON; 5 STORES DESTROYED IN STRIP MALL FIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A two-alarm fire raced through a strip mall Saturday night, gutting five 
stores and causing about $1 million in damage, fire officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Fire Department officials are still investigating the cause of the 11:40 p.m. 
blaze at the shopping center in the 1600 block of West Orangethorpe Avenue. No 
one was reported injured. 
</P>
<P>
 Twenty firefighters from Fullerton, Anaheim and Orange worked for more than an 
hour to control the blaze, which destroyed two restaurants, a boot store, a 
jewelry boutique and a beauty supply shop. 
</P>
<P>
 Six other stores and a supermarket in the strip mall were spared, fire 
officials said. 
</P>
