<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: WESTMINSTER; SALARY, OUTLINE OKD FOR 2 FIRE POSITIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council has unanimously approved the job description and salary range 
for two management positions in the Fire Department. 
</P>
<P>
 For assistant fire chief, the council approved a salary of $6,477 to $7,825 
per month.For division chief of administration and fire prevention, the salary 
range is from $6,214 to $7,249 monthly. 
</P>
<P>
 The two new positions were created as part of the reorganization of the Fire 
Department, which the council approved last year. 
</P>
<P>
 The assistant fire chief will handle general operations, attend to personnel 
matters including discipline, and serve as acting fire chief in the absence of 
the fire chief. 
</P>
<P>
 The administration and fire prevention division chief will coordinate the 
department's training, paramedic services and administration of clerical 
employees. In addition, he or she will be in charge of fire prevention programs 
and fire investigations. 
</P>
<P>
 Fire Chief John T. DeMonaco Jr. said that the positions likely will be filled 
by current department employees but that outsiders will also be considered. 
BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</TEXT>
